Dietary Supplements as Surrogate of Mediterranean Diet in Healthy Smoking 
Subjects.

Vasto S(1)(2), Accardi G(3), Aiello A(3), Di Gaudio F(3)(4)(5), Barera A(3), 
Indelicato S(5), Galimberti D(6), Italiano E(7), Monastero R(8), Rizzo C(3), 
Caruso C(3)(6), Candore G(3).

Author information:
(1)1 Department of Biological Chemical and Pharmaceutical Sciences and 
Technologies, University of Palermo , Viale delle Scienze, Palermo, Italy .
(2)2 Institute of Biomedicine and Molecular Immunology "Alberto Monroy" , 
National Research Council, Palermo, Italy .
(3)3 General Pathology Unit, Department of Pathobiology and Medical 
Biotechnologies, University of Palermo , Palermo, Italy .
(4)4 Institute for the Study of Nanostructured Materials , National Research 
Council, Palermo, Italy .
(5)5 Quality Control Laboratories and Chemical Risk, University Hospital Paolo 
Giaccone , Palermo, Italy .
(6)6 Italian Association of Anti-Ageing Physicians , Milan, Italy .
(7)7 Operative Unit of Urology, Hospital "Villa Sofia-Cervello," Piazzetta 
